	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">WEST virginia legislature</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 regular session</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">ENROLLED</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Committee Substitute</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">for</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4755</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Ridenour, Kump, Butler, Masters, Hillenbrand, Funkhouser, Ward, Mallow, Kimble, and Martin </span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Passed March 14, 2026; in effect 90 days from passage (June 12, 2026)]</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="csBE88CC83"><span class="csEF05ACC">AN ACT to amend and reenact &sect;61-11-18 of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, relating to qualifying offenses for purposes of recidivism punishment; adding aggravated vehicular homicide, driving under the influence causing serious bodily injury, third offense driving under the influence, and obstructing law enforcement, fire personnel, and emergency medical personnel causing death as qualifying offenses for enhanced sentencing of a repeat offender; and creating criminal penalties. </span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 11. GENERAL PROVISIONS CONCERNING CRIMES.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;61-11-18. Punishment for second or third offense of felony.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(a) For purposes of this section, &quot;qualifying offense&quot; means any offense or an attempt or conspiracy to commit any of the offenses in the following provisions of this code:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(1) &sect;17C-5-1(c): Aggravated vehicular homicide; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(2) &sect;17C-5-2(b): Driving under the influence causing death;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(3) &sect;17C-5-2(c): Driving under the influence causing serious bodily injury; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(4) &sect;17C-5-2(m): Third offense driving under the influence;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(5) &sect;60A-4-401(a)(i) and &sect;60A-4-401(a)(ii): Manufacturing or delivery of a Schedule ! or II controlled substance which is a narcotic drug or methamphetamine; manufacturing or delivery of any other Schedule I, II, or III drug;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(6) &sect;60A-4-406: Distribution to persons under the age of 18 by persons over the age of 21; distribution by persons 18 or over in, on, or within 1,000 feet of, school or college; distribution by persons 18 or over in, on, or within 200 feet of a public library;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(7) &sect;60A-4-409(b)(1), &sect;60A-4-409(b)(2), &sect;60A-4-409(c), &sect;60A-4-409(d), and &sect;60A-4-409(e): Prohibited acts relating to transportation of controlled substances into state;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(8) &sect;60A-4-411: Operating or attempting to operate clandestine drug laboratories;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(9) &sect;60A-4-414: Conspiracy;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(10) &sect;60A-4-416(a): Drug delivery resulting in death;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(11) &sect;60A-4-419: Drug kingpin;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(12) &sect;61-2-1: First and second degree murder;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(13) &sect;61-2-4: Voluntary manslaughter;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(14) &sect;61-2-7: Attempt to kill or injure by poison;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(15) &sect;61-2-9(a): Malicious assault; unlawful assault;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(16) &sect;61-2-9a(d) and &sect;61-2-9a(e): Second or subsequent offense stalking or harassment; stalking or harassment in violation of a protective order;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(17) &sect;61-2-9b: Malicious or unlawful assault of a child near a school;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(18) &sect;61-2-9c: Wanton endangerment involving the use of fire;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(19) &sect;61-2-9d: Strangulation, suffocation, and asphyxiation;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(20) &sect;61-2-10: Assault during commission of or attempt to commit a felony;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(21) &sect;61-2-10b(b) and &sect;61-2-10b(c): Malicious and unlawful assault on governmental representatives, health care providers, utility workers, law-enforcement officers, correctional employees and emergency medical service personnel;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(22) Felony provisions of &sect;61-2-10b(d): Battery on a government representative, health care worker, utility worker, emergency service personnel, correctional employee or law-enforcement officer;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(23) &sect;61-2-12: Robbery or attempted robbery;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(24) Felony provisions of &sect;61-2-13: Extortion or attempted extortion by threats;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(25) &sect;61-2-14: Abduction of person, kidnapping or concealing child;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(26) &sect;61-2-14a(a) and &sect;61-2-14a(d): Kidnapping;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(27) &sect;61-2-14c: Threats to kidnap or demand ransom;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(28) &sect;61-2-14d(a) and &sect;61-2-14d(b): Concealment or removal of minor child from custodian or from person entitled to visitation;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(29) &sect;61-2-14f: Penalties for abduction of a child near a school;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(30) &sect;61-2-14h(a), &sect;61-2-14h(b), and &sect;61-2-14h(c): Purchase or sale of child;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(31) &sect;61-2-16a(a) and &sect;61-2-16a(b): Malicious assault and unlawful assault on a driver, conductor, motorman, captain, pilot or other person in charge of any vehicle used for public conveyance;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(32) Felony provisions of &sect;61-2-16a(c): Second offense battery on a driver, conductor, motorman, captain, pilot or other person in charge of any vehicle used for public conveyance;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(33) &sect;61-2-28(d): Domestic battery and assault, third or subsequent offense;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(34) &sect;61-2-29(d) and &sect;61-2-29(e): Abuse or neglect of an incapacitated adult;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(35) &sect;61-2-29a: Death of an incapacitated adult by a caregiver;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(36) &sect;61-3-1: Burning, etc., of a dwelling or outbuilding; first degree arson;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(37) &sect;61-3-2: Burning, etc., of other buildings or structures; second degree arson;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(38) &sect;61-3-3: Burning personal property of another of the value of five hundred dollars or more; third degree arson;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(39) &sect;61-3-4: Attempt to commit arson; fourth degree arson;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(40) &sect;61-3-5: Burning, or attempting to burn, insured property;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(41) &sect;61-3-6: Willfully, unlawfully and maliciously setting fire on lands;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(42) &sect;61-3-7: Causing injuries during an arson-related crime;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(43) &sect;61-3-11: Burglary; entry of dwelling or outhouse;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(44) Felony violation of &sect;61-3-12: Entry of building other than dwelling; entry of railroad, traction or motorcar, steamboat, or other vessel;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(45) &sect;61-3-13(a): Grand larceny;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><a name="_Hlk159225632"><span class="csEF05ACC">(46) Felony violation of</span></a><span class="csEF05ACC"> &sect;61-3-18: Receiving or transferring stolen goods;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(47) Felony violation of &sect;61-3-19: Bringing into this state, receiving or disposing of property stolen in another state;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(48) Felony violation of &sect;61-3-20: Embezzlement; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(49) Felony violation of &sect;61-3-20a: Embezzlement by misuse of power of attorney or other fiduciary relationship;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(50) Felony violation of &sect;61-3-21: Embezzlement by carrier or other person;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(51) &sect;61-3-22: Falsifying accounts; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(52) Felony violation of &sect;61-3-24: Obtaining money, property and services by false pretenses; disposing of property to defraud creditors;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(53) Felony violation of &sect;61-3-24a: Attempted or fraudulent use, forgery, traffic of credit cards; possession and transfer of credit cards and credit card making equipment; false or fraudulent use of telephonic services;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(54) &sect;61-3-27: Malicious killing of animals by poison or otherwise;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(55) &sect;61-3-54: Taking identity of another person;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(56) &sect;61-3C-14b: Soliciting, etc. a minor via computer, soliciting a minor and traveling to engage the minor in prohibited sexual activity;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(57) &sect;61-3E-5: Causing death or injury;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(58) Felony violation of &sect;61-5-10: Persons in custody of institutions or officers;</span></p><p class="cs7788C6BC"><span class="csEF05ACC">(59) Felony provisions of &sect;61-5-17: Obstructing officer; fleeing from officer; making</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">false statements to officer; interfering with emergency communications; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(60) &sect;61-5-17a: Obstructing a law-enforcement officer, probation officer, parole officer, courthouse security officer, correctional officer, the State Fire Marshal, a deputy or assistant fire marshal, firefighter, or emergency medical service personnel causing death;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(61) &sect;61-5-27: Intimidation of and retaliation against public officers and employees, jurors, and witnesses; fraudulent official proceedings and legal processes against public officials and employees; making public threats directed at inciting lawless action;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(62) &sect;61-6-24: Threats of terrorist acts, conveying false information concerning terrorist acts and committing terrorist hoaxes prohibited;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(63) Felony provisions of &sect;61-7-7: Persons prohibited from possessing firearms;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(64) &sect;61-7-12: Wanton endangerment involving a firearm;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(65) &sect;61-7-15: Persons prohibited from committing violent crime while wearing body armor;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(66) &sect;61-7-15a: Use or presentation of a firearm during commission of a felony;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(67) &sect;61-8-12: Incest;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(68) &sect;61-8-19(b): Cruelty to animals;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(69) &sect;61-8A-2: Distribution and display to minor of obscene matter;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(70) &sect;61-8A-4: Use of obscene matter with intent to seduce minor;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(71) &sect;61-8A-5: Employment or use of minor to produce obscene matter or assist in doing sexually explicit conduct;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(72) &sect;61-8B-3: Sexual assault in the first degree;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(73) &sect;61-8B-4: Sexual assault in the second degree;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(74) &sect;61-8B-5: Sexual assault in the third degree;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(75) &sect;61-8B-7: Sexual abuse in the first degree;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(76) &sect;61-8B-10: Imposition of sexual acts on persons incarcerated, detained, or under supervision;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(77) &sect;61-8B-11b: Prohibiting sexual intercourse, sexual intrusion, or sexual contact, against students by school employees;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(78) &sect;61-8C-2: Use of minors in filming sexually explicit conduct prohibited;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(79) &sect;61-8C-3: Distribution and exhibiting of material depicting minors engaged in sexually explicit conduct or computer-generated child pornography prohibited;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(80) &sect;61-8C-3a: Prohibiting child erotica;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(81) &sect;61-8D-2: Murder of a child by a parent, guardian or custodian or other person, or person in a position of trust in relation to a child, by refusal or failure to supply necessities, or by delivery, administration or ingestion of a controlled substance;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(82) &sect;61-8D-2a: Death of a child by a parent, guardian or custodian or other person or person in a position of trust in relation to a child, by child abuse;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(83) &sect;61-8D-3: Child abuse resulting in injury; child abuse creating risk of injury;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(84) &sect;61-8D-3a: Female genital mutilation;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(85) &sect;61-8D-4: Child neglect resulting in injury; child neglect creating risk of injury;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(86) &sect;61-8D-4a: Child neglect resulting in death;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(87) &sect;61-8D-5: Sexual abuse by a parent, guardian, custodian or person in a position of trust to a child; parent, guardian, custodian or person in a position of trust allowing sexual abuse to be inflicted upon a child; displaying of sex organs by a parent, guardian, or custodian;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(88) &sect;61-8D-6: Sending, distributing, exhibiting, possessing, displaying or transporting material by a parent, guardian or custodian, depicting a child engaged in sexually explicit conduct;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;(89) &sect;61-10-31: Conspiracy;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(90) &sect;61-11-8: Attempts;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(91) &sect;61-11-8a: Solicitation to commit certain felonies; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(92) &sect;61-14-2: Human trafficking of an individual; aiding and abetting human trafficking. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(b) Except as provided by subsection (c) of this section, when any person is convicted of a qualifying offense and is subject to imprisonment in a state correctional facility for the qualifying offender and it is determined, as provided in &sect;61-11-19 of this code, that the person had been previously convicted in the United States of a crime punishable by imprisonment in a state or federal correctional facility, the court shall, if the sentence to be imposed is for a definite term of years, add five years to the time for which the person is or would be otherwise sentenced. Whenever in that case the court imposes an indeterminate sentence, the minimum term shall be twice the term of years otherwise provided for under the sentence.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(c) Notwithstanding any provision of this code to the contrary, when any person is convicted of first degree murder or second degree murder or a violation of &sect;61-8B-3 of this code and it is determined, as provided in &sect;61-11-19 of this code, that the person had been previously convicted in this state of first degree murder, second degree murder, or a violation of &sect;61-8B-3 of this code, or has been so convicted under any law of the United States or any other state for an offense which has the same or substantially similar elements as any offense described in this subsection, the person shall be punished by imprisonment in a state correctional facility for life and is not eligible for parole.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(d) When it is determined, as provided in &sect;61-11-19 of this code, that the person has been twice previously convicted in the United States of a crime punishable by imprisonment in a state or federal correctional facility which has the same or substantially similar elements as a qualifying offense, the person shall be sentenced to imprisonment in a state correctional facility for life:&nbsp;</span><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Provided</span><span class="csEF05ACC">, That prior convictions arising from the same transaction or series of transactions shall be considered a single offense for purposes of this section:&nbsp;</span><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Provided, however</span><span class="csEF05ACC">, That the most recent previous qualifying offense which would otherwise constitute a qualifying offense for purposes of this subsection may not be considered if more than 20 years have elapsed between: (1) The release of the person from his or her term of imprisonment or period of supervision resulting from the most recent qualifying offense or the expiration of a period of supervised release resulting from the offense; and (2) the conduct underlying the current charge.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs2CFA8611"><span class="csEF05ACC">The Clerk of the House of Delegates and the Clerk of the Senate hereby certify that the foregoing bill is correctly enrolled.</span></p><p class="cs53BAC856"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs53BAC856"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p cla